OL,3,CEnergy price cap rise: What this mean
OL,4,Cfor your bills and how to keep costs
OL,5,Cdown
OL,7,FOfgem changes the price cap for
OL,8,Fhouseholds every three months, largely
OL,9,Fbased on the cost of energy on
OL,10,Fwholesale markets.
OL,12,FIt does not limit total bills because
OL,13,Fhouseholders still pay for the amount
OL,14,Fof energy they consume.
